            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the bacon lardons have started to brown, add the<strong> halved cherry tomatoes</strong>,<strong> sliced garlic</strong>,<strong> dried oregano</strong> and<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan and cook for 3-4 min further</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> and <strong>tomato paste </strong>in 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[100ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>– this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1684853957993-x200.jpg",
